Legal Aspects of e-Repositories and e-Collections Conference
31 May - 1 June 2006,  Scarman House, University of Warwick

This year's JISC Legal conference will deal with=20
the legal issues relevant to the establishment,=20
development and use of e-repositories and=20
e-collections in the UK=92s further and higher=20
education sectors.  The conference will consider=20
the law in relation to digital collection=20
building at all levels, whether in the shape of=20
institutional repositories and depositories,=20
regional and national depositories, project and=20
thematic depositories, library e-collections, and=20
even course-specific online material collections.

We are pleased to announce that Dr Malcolm Read,=20
the Executive Secretary of JISC, has agreed to chair the proceedings.

The event will look at the following issues:

=95 Ensuring copyright compliance with respect to material deposited
=95 Ensuring robust licensing of materials for use
=95 Dealing with copyright in cases of adaptation for reuse
=95 The legal consequences of digital rights management systems
=95 The database right in relation to e-repositories and e-collections
=95 The extent of an e-repository=92s liability for breach of copyright
=95 The extent of an e-repository=92s liability for defamation
=95 The law regarding accessibility, disability=20
discrimination and e-repositories and e-collections
=95 The submission of personal data in=20
e-repositories, and the consequences of data protection law

In addition, there will be particular case=20
studies considering copyright, licensing and=20
e-repositories at different levels, and=20
particular workshops in relation to medical, art and research=
 e-repositories.

Early booking is advised to secure a place on the=20
conference as numbers will be restricted due to=20
seating availability in lecture=20
theatre.  Accommodation and a social event are=20
also available for the evening of Tuesday, 30=20
May, if you want to avoid an early start.

Link to programme details:=20
<http://www.jisclegal.ac.uk/events/eRep_06/Programme.htm>http://www.jisclega=
l.ac.uk/events/eRep_06/Programme.htm.

Online booking form:  The conference can now be=20
booked online at -=20
<http://www.jisclegal.ac.uk/events/eRep_06/Booking_Form.htm>http://www.jiscl=
egal.ac.uk/events/eRep_06/Booking_Form.htm

We look forward to receiving your booking and seeing you there!.

In the meantime, if you have any queries, please=20
email us at=20
<mailto:events@jisclegal.ac.uk>events@jisclegal.ac.uk=20
or call us on 0141 548 4939.

